  "text": "In order to find the action maximizing the long-term reward in a state s, it is common to maximize the expected discounted gain following a policy π from a state, noted V π (s), or from a state-action tuple, noted Q π (s, a) (cf. equation 3). It enables to measure the impact of the stateaction tuple in obtaining the cumulative reward [CITATION_1] ].",
